The paper deals with the problem of enabling human operators to control multiple robots, which is a core problem in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves modeling the user's decision-making process and preferences, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of simulation experiments and a user study, which are common methods in systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA).
